d since the 1980s."],"variants":[{"name":"Danyal","meanings":["Fanciful respelling of   Daniel ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":76,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":85,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Daniel Skarlett was born in 1473, in Charlton, Somerset, England. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Daniel Skarlett. He died in 1566, at the age of 93."},"et":{"1473–1566":"1473–1566","1474–Female":"1474–Surnud","1500–1594":"1500–1594","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","1566":"1566","1474":"1474","1473":"1473","1594":"1594","1549":"1549","Charlton, Somerset, England":"Charlton, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1473–1566":"1473–1566","1474–Female":"1474–Kuollut","1500–1594":"1500–1594","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","1566":"1566","1474":"1474","1473":"1473","1594":"1594","1549":"1549","Charlton, Somerset, England":"Charlton, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"1473–1566":"1473–1566","1474–Female":"1474–Décédée","1500–1594":"1500–1594","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","1566":"1566","1474":"1474","1473":"1473","1594":"1594","1549":"1549","Charlton, Somerset, England":"Charlton, Somerset, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Daniel Sk